Definition: a mere semblance of legal right
Example: something done with the apparent authority of law but actually in contravention of law; the plaintiff claimed that under color of law the officer had deprived him of his civil rights
Synonyms: colour_of_law, semblance, noun, group, law, c, a, mere, of, legal, right, something, done, with, the, apparent, authority, but, actually, in, contravention, plaintiff, claimed, that, under, color, officer, had, deprived, him, his, civil, rights
Category: noun.attribute
